{
  "video_id": "Vn6elsrKz70",
  "title": "3 ways to practice civility | Steven Petrow",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12857.0,
      "end_time": 15500.0,
      "text": "I want to start by telling you two things about myself"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 15524.0,
      "end_time": 17657.0,
      "text": "before I get into the full talk."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 18400.0,
      "end_time": 21183.0,
      "text": "And the first is that I&#39;ve been writing about manners and civility"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 21208.0,
      "end_time": 22378.0,
      "text": "for more than 20 years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 22403.0,
      "end_time": 24869.0,
      "text": "as a book author and as a magazine columnist."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 25902.0,
      "end_time": 27672.0,
      "text": "The second is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 27696.0,
      "end_time": 32530.0,
      "text": "my friends know to be very wary of inviting me over for dinner"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 32554.000000000004,
      "end_time": 34864.0,
      "text": "because any faux pas that happens at the table"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 34888.0,
      "end_time": 36539.0,
      "text": "is likely to wind up in print."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 36563.0,
      "end_time": 37657.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 37681.0,
      "end_time": 41482.0,
      "text": "So, I&#39;m watching, I can see back there and I can see through the portals, too."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 41506.0,
      "end_time": 42656.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 43855.0,
      "end_time": 45782.0,
      "text": "So, speaking of dinner parties,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 45807.0,
      "end_time": 49950.0,
      "text": "I want to take you back to 2015 and a dinner party that I went to."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 51395.0,
      "end_time": 53770.0,
      "text": "To place this in time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 53101.0,
      "end_time": 56205.0,
      "text": "this was when Caitlyn Jenner was first coming out,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 56230.0,
      "end_time": 58809.0,
      "text": "shedding her identity as a Kardashian"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 58833.0,
      "end_time": 61888.0,
      "text": "and moving into her life as a transgender activist."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 62230.0,
      "end_time": 64574.0,
      "text": "I wrote a column in People magazine at the time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 64598.0,
      "end_time": 66561.0,
      "text": "talking about the importance of names"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 66585.0,
      "end_time": 69306.0,
      "text": "and how names are our identity."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 69784.0,
      "end_time": 73768.0,
      "text": "And that to misuse them or not to use them erases us in a certain way."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 73792.0,
      "end_time": 75712.0,
      "text": "And especially with Caitlyn Jenner,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 75736.0,
      "end_time": 79101.0,
      "text": "I talked about Caitlyn, but also the use of her pronouns."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 79125.0,
      "end_time": 80275.0,
      "text": "Her pronouns."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 80744.0,
      "end_time": 83387.0,
      "text": "So I&#39;m at this dinner -- delicious, wonderful, fun --"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 83411.0,
      "end_time": 87824.0,
      "text": "when my host goes on a rant about Caitlyn Jenner."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 88706.0,
      "end_time": 93842.0,
      "text": "And she is saying that it is disrespectful for Caitlyn Jenner"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 93866.0,
      "end_time": 98416.0,
      "text": "to force her to use a new name and to use these new pronouns."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 99530.0,
      "end_time": 100713.0,
      "text": "She&#39;s not buying it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 100737.0,
      "end_time": 103871.0,
      "text": "and I&#39;m listening, and because I do meditation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 103895.0,
      "end_time": 106714.0,
      "text": "I took my sacred pause before I responded."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 106738.0,
      "end_time": 107888.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 109962.0,
      "end_time": 112319.0,
      "text": "And I reminded her that when she got married,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 112343.0,
      "end_time": 114105.0,
      "text": "she changed her name,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 114129.0,
      "end_time": 116422.0,
      "text": "and that she took the name of her husband."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 116446.0,
      "end_time": 118979.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s the name all of us now use."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 119466.0,
      "end_time": 121776.0,
      "text": "We don&#39;t use it just because it&#39;s her legal name,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 121800.0,
      "end_time": 123640.0,
      "text": "but we use it because it&#39;s respectful."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 124530.0,
      "end_time": 125520.0,
      "text": "Ditto for Miss Jenner."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 126268.0,
      "end_time": 128529.0,
      "text": "She didn&#39;t buy it and we didn&#39;t speak for years."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 128553.0,
      "end_time": 130377.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 130887.0,
      "end_time": 132173.0,
      "text": "So ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 133538.0,
      "end_time": 135823.0,
      "text": "I am known as the Civilist."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 135847.0,
      "end_time": 139514.0,
      "text": "And it&#39;s probably a word that you&#39;re not that familiar with."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 140530.0,
      "end_time": 141515.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s not in common parlance"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 141539.0,
      "end_time": 144560.0,
      "text": "and it comes from the Latin and the French,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 144585.0,
      "end_time": 148656.0,
      "text": "and it means an individual who tries to live by a moral code,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 148680.0,
      "end_time": 151147.0,
      "text": "who is striving to be a good citizen."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 151863.0,
      "end_time": 154466.0,
      "text": "The word \"civility\" is derived from that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 154490.0,
      "end_time": 156752.0,
      "text": "and the original definition of civility"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 156776.0,
      "end_time": 160934.0,
      "text": "is citizens willing to give of themselves for the good of the city,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 160958.0,
      "end_time": 163879.0,
      "text": "for the good of the commonwealth, for the larger good."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 164427.0,
      "end_time": 165584.0,
      "text": "So, in this talk,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 165609.0,
      "end_time": 169511.0,
      "text": "you&#39;re going to learn three new ways to be civil, I hope,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 169535.0,
      "end_time": 173863.0,
      "text": "and it will be according to the original definition of civility."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 174394.0,
      "end_time": 176350.0,
      "text": "My first problem is:"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 177403.0,
      "end_time": 179335.0,
      "text": "civility is an obsolete word."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 179684.0,
      "end_time": 181763.0,
      "text": "My second problem is:"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 181787.0,
      "end_time": 184192.0,
      "text": "civility has become a dirty word in this country."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 184708.0,
      "end_time": 187834.0,
      "text": "And that is whether you lean right or whether you lean left."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 188410.0,
      "end_time": 193768.0,
      "text": "And in part, that&#39;s because modern usage equates civility with decorum,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 193792.0,
      "end_time": 196537.0,
      "text": "with formal politeness, formal behavior."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 197196.0,
      "end_time": 199942.0,
      "text": "We&#39;ve gotten away from the idea of citizenship."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 200792.0,
      "end_time": 204672.0,
      "text": "So, let me start by talking a little bit about my friends on the right,"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 204696.0,
      "end_time": 208216.0,
      "text": "who have conflated civility with what they call political correctness."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 208982.0,
      "end_time": 211470.0,
      "text": "And to them, callouts for civility"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 211710.0,
      "end_time": 215395.0,
      "text": "are really very much like what George Orwell wrote in \"1984\" --"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 215419.0,
      "end_time": 216688.0,
      "text": "he called it \"newspeak.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 217188.0,
      "end_time": 220679.0,
      "text": "And this was an attempt to change the way we talk"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 220704.0,
      "end_time": 223690.0,
      "text": "by forcibly changing the language that we use."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 223930.0,
      "end_time": 226930.0,
      "text": "To change our ideas by changing the meaning of words."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 226784.0,
      "end_time": 230117.0,
      "text": "And I think my dinner host might have had some of that"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 230141.0,
      "end_time": 231441.0,
      "text": "rattling around there."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 233577.0,
      "end_time": 235713.0,
      "text": "And I first personally understood, though,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 235737.0,
      "end_time": 237384.0,
      "text": "the right&#39;s problem with civility"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 237408.0,
      "end_time": 240850.0,
      "text": "when I wrote a column about then-candidate Donald Trump."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 241284.0,
      "end_time": 243298.0,
      "text": "And he had just said"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 243323.0,
      "end_time": 247530.0,
      "text": "he did not have time for total political correctness,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 247770.0,
      "end_time": 249316.0,
      "text": "and he did not believe the country did either."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 249340.0,
      "end_time": 253474.0,
      "text": "And I took that to heart, it was very --"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 254498.0,
      "end_time": 257695.0,
      "text": "The audience was very engaged about that online, as you can imagine."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 257720.00000000003,
      "end_time": 262220.0,
      "text": "There was a thousand responses, and this one stood out to me"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 262244.0,
      "end_time": 264244.0,
      "text": "because it was representative:"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 265930.0,
      "end_time": 268339.0,
      "text": "\"Political correctness is a pathological system"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 268363.0,
      "end_time": 270807.0,
      "text": "that lets liberals dominate a conversation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 270831.0,
      "end_time": 273964.0,
      "text": "label, demonize and shout down the opposition.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 275228.0,
      "end_time": 279696.0,
      "text": "So I think, to the right, civility translates into censure."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 281117.0,
      "end_time": 282450.0,
      "text": "So that&#39;s the right."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 283211.0,
      "end_time": 286863.0,
      "text": "Now, my friends on the left also have a problem with it."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 287323.0,
      "end_time": 289150.0,
      "text": "And for example, there have been those"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 289174.0,
      "end_time": 291561.0,
      "text": "who have harassed Trump administration officials"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 291585.0,
      "end_time": 294275.0,
      "text": "who support the President&#39;s border wall."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 294855.0,
      "end_time": 298300.0,
      "text": "They&#39;ve been called out as rude, they&#39;ve been called out as nasty,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 298540.0,
      "end_time": 299655.0,
      "text": "they&#39;ve been called out as worse."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 299680.0,
      "end_time": 301912.0,
      "text": "And after one such incident last year,"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 301936.0,
      "end_time": 303810.0,
      "text": "even the Washington Post --"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 303834.0,
      "end_time": 305892.0,
      "text": "you know, left-leaning Washington Post --"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 305916.0,
      "end_time": 308720.0,
      "text": "wrote an editorial and sided with decorum."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 308971.0,
      "end_time": 312622.0,
      "text": "And they argued that officials should be allowed to dine in peace."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 313828.0,
      "end_time": 314977.0,
      "text": "Hm."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 315574.0,
      "end_time": 318774.0,
      "text": "\"You know, the wall is the real incivility here."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 319790.0,
      "end_time": 322950.0,
      "text": "The tear-gassing of kids, the separation of families.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 322595.0,
      "end_time": 324389.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s what the protestors say."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 325579.0,
      "end_time": 327685.0,
      "text": "And imagine if we had sided, in this country,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 327709.0,
      "end_time": 330943.0,
      "text": "with decorum and courtesy throughout our history."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 331306.0,
      "end_time": 333615.0,
      "text": "You know, I think about the suffragettes."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 334275.0,
      "end_time": 336558.0,
      "text": "They marched, they picketed."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 337101.0,
      "end_time": 339656.0,
      "text": "They were chastised, they were arrested"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 339680.0,
      "end_time": 342452.0,
      "text": "for pursuing the vote for women in the 1920s."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 342934.0,
      "end_time": 346180.0,
      "text": "You know, I also think about the Reverend Martin Luther King Jr.,"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 346204.0,
      "end_time": 349458.0,
      "text": "the father of American nonviolent civil disobedience."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 349784.0,
      "end_time": 355187.0,
      "text": "He was labeled as uncivil in his attempt to promote racial and economic justice."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 356916.0,
      "end_time": 358241.0,
      "text": "So I think you get a sense"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 358265.0,
      "end_time": 362292.0,
      "text": "of why civility has become a problem, a dirty word, here."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 363820.0,
      "end_time": 368700.0,
      "text": "Now, does this mean we can&#39;t disagree, that we can&#39;t speak our minds?"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 368585.0,
      "end_time": 370920.0,
      "text": "Absolutely not."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 370775.0,
      "end_time": 373174.0,
      "text": "I recently spoke with Dr. Carolyn Lukensmeyer."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 373514.0,
      "end_time": 376347.0,
      "text": "She&#39;s kind of the guru of civility in this country,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 376371.0,
      "end_time": 378205.0,
      "text": "and the executive director of a body"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 378229.0,
      "end_time": 380695.0,
      "text": "called the National Institute for Civil Discourse."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 380720.0,
      "end_time": 381871.0,
      "text": "And she told me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 381895.0,
      "end_time": 386236.0,
      "text": "\"Civility does not mean appeasement or avoiding important differences."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 386260.0,
      "end_time": 390522.0,
      "text": "It means listening and talking about those differences with respect.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 392696.0,
      "end_time": 395903.0,
      "text": "In a healthy democracy, we need to do that."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 395927.0,
      "end_time": 398460.0,
      "text": "And I call that respectful engagement."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 399101.0,
      "end_time": 402340.0,
      "text": "But civil discourse also needs rules, it needs boundaries."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 403869.0,
      "end_time": 406139.0,
      "text": "For instance, there&#39;s a difference"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 406163.0,
      "end_time": 409504.0,
      "text": "between language that is simply rude or demeaning,"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 409528.0,
      "end_time": 413930.0,
      "text": "and speech that invokes hatred and intolerance."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 413117.0,
      "end_time": 415290.0,
      "text": "And specifically of groups."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 415530.0,
      "end_time": 417156.0,
      "text": "And I&#39;m thinking of racial and ethnic groups,"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 417180.0,
      "end_time": 419379.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m thinking of the LGBTQ community,"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 419403.0,
      "end_time": 421180.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m thinking of the disabled."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 422523.0,
      "end_time": 425684.0,
      "text": "We snowflakes call this speech \"hate speech.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 426318.0,
      "end_time": 428967.0,
      "text": "And hate speech can lead to violence."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 431480.0,
      "end_time": 434713.0,
      "text": "So, to that point, in the fall of 2018,"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 434737.0,
      "end_time": 437893.0,
      "text": "I wrote a column about Dr. Christine Blasey Ford."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 438269.0,
      "end_time": 439483.0,
      "text": "You may remember her,"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 439507.0,
      "end_time": 444150.0,
      "text": "she was one of the women who accused Supreme Court nominee Brett Kavanaugh"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 444390.0,
      "end_time": 445239.0,
      "text": "of sexual assault."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 445737.0,
      "end_time": 447212.0,
      "text": "And among the responses,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 447236.0,
      "end_time": 450236.0,
      "text": "I received this message, a personal message,"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 450968.0,
      "end_time": 453285.0,
      "text": "which you can see here on the slide."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 453309.0,
      "end_time": 455550.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s been largely redacted."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 455790.0,
      "end_time": 456299.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 456323.0,
      "end_time": 459758.0,
      "text": "This message was 50 words long. 10 of them were the f-bomb."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 460498.0,
      "end_time": 464178.0,
      "text": "And the Democrats were called out, President Obama was called out,"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 464202.0,
      "end_time": 467863.0,
      "text": "and I was referred to in a pretty darn vulgar and coarse way."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 471258.0,
      "end_time": 473680.0,
      "text": "There was an explicit threat in that message,"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 473704.0,
      "end_time": 476847.0,
      "text": "and that is why my editors at The Post sent it to authorities."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 478108.0,
      "end_time": 481704.0,
      "text": "This came shortly before the pipe bombs were sent to other media outlets,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 481728.0,
      "end_time": 484513.0,
      "text": "so everybody was really kind of on guard there."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 486252.0,
      "end_time": 489212.0,
      "text": "And the larger context was, only a few months before,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 489236.0,
      "end_time": 491815.0,
      "text": "five staffers had been killed at a Maryland newspaper."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 491839.0,
      "end_time": 495276.0,
      "text": "They had been shot dead by a reader with a grudge."
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 496174.0,
      "end_time": 498700.0,
      "text": "\"Shut up or else.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 500340.0,
      "end_time": 503133.0,
      "text": "And it was around that same time"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 503158.0,
      "end_time": 506284.0,
      "text": "that a different reader of mine started stalking me online."
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 506308.0,
      "end_time": 507824.0,
      "text": "And at first, it was ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 508737.0,
      "end_time": 510170.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ll call it light and fluffy."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 510194.0,
      "end_time": 511785.0,
      "text": "It was around this time last year"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 511809.0,
      "end_time": 513872.0,
      "text": "and I still had my Christmas decorations up"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 513895.0,
      "end_time": 515871.0,
      "text": "and he sent me a message saying,"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 515895.0,
      "end_time": 518592.0,
      "text": "\"You should take your Christmas decorations down.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 518616.0,
      "end_time": 521318.0,
      "text": "And then he noticed that my dog was off leash one day,"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 521342.0,
      "end_time": 523808.0,
      "text": "and then he commented that I had gone to the market."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 525576.0,
      "end_time": 528910.0,
      "text": "And then he wrote me one that said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 528115.0,
      "end_time": 530328.0,
      "text": "\"If anyone were to shoot and kill you,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 530352.0,
      "end_time": 532172.0,
      "text": "it would not be a loss at all.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 534450.0,
      "end_time": 536434.0,
      "text": "I wish that were the end of the story."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 536458.0,
      "end_time": 539709.0,
      "text": "Because then, a few months later, he came to my door, my front door,"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 539734.0,
      "end_time": 542182.0,
      "text": "in a rage and tried to break the door down."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 542206.0,
      "end_time": 545150.0,
      "text": "I now own mace, a security system"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 545174.0,
      "end_time": 547848.0,
      "text": "and a Louisville Slugger baseball bat."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 548792.0,
      "end_time": 549942.0,
      "text": "(Sighs)"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 550539.0,
      "end_time": 552470.0,
      "text": "\"Shut up or else.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 552935.0,
      "end_time": 554108.0,
      "text": "So, what&#39;s to be done"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 554133.0,
      "end_time": 557273.0,
      "text": "to forestall civility from turning ugly, from turning violent?"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 557887.0,
      "end_time": 560370.0,
      "text": "My first rule is to deescalate language."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 560620.0,
      "end_time": 563508.0,
      "text": "And I&#39;ve stopped using trigger words in print."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 564332.0,
      "end_time": 567295.0,
      "text": "And by trigger words, I mean \"homophobe,\" I mean \"racist,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 567319.0,
      "end_time": 570141.0,
      "text": "I mean \"xenophobe,\" I mean \"sexist.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 570165.0,
      "end_time": 571432.0,
      "text": "All of those words."
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 572260.0,
      "end_time": 573982.0,
      "text": "They set people off."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 574561.0,
      "end_time": 575713.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re incendiary"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 575737.0,
      "end_time": 578243.0,
      "text": "and they do not allow us to find common ground."
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 578268.0,
      "end_time": 580890.0,
      "text": "They do not allow us to find a common heart."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 581553.0,
      "end_time": 585717.0,
      "text": "And so to this point, when John McCain died in 2018,"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 587196.0,
      "end_time": 591132.0,
      "text": "his supporters noted that he never made personal attacks."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 591448.0,
      "end_time": 593107.0,
      "text": "But his opponents agreed as well,"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 593131.0,
      "end_time": 595424.0,
      "text": "and I though that was what was really noteworthy."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 595448.0,
      "end_time": 598424.0,
      "text": "He challenged people&#39;s policies, he challenged their positions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 598448.0,
      "end_time": 599900.0,
      "text": "but he never made it personal."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 600289.0,
      "end_time": 602289.0,
      "text": "And so that&#39;s the second rule."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 603275.0,
      "end_time": 607310.0,
      "text": "So the problem of civility is not only an American one."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 607504.0,
      "end_time": 611314.0,
      "text": "In the Netherlands, there are calls for a civility offensive right now,"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 611338.0,
      "end_time": 613677.0,
      "text": "and as one Dutch philosopher has put it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 613701.0,
      "end_time": 617690.0,
      "text": "the country has fallen under a spell of \"verhuftering.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 617614.0,
      "end_time": 621494.0,
      "text": "Now, this is not a word that I knew before and I did quite a bit of research."
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 621900.0,
      "end_time": 626158.0,
      "text": "It loosely means bullying and the disappearance of good manners."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 626552.0,
      "end_time": 630249.0,
      "text": "It actually means much worse than that, but that&#39;s what I&#39;m saying here."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 631228.0,
      "end_time": 634853.0,
      "text": "When you have a specific word, though, to describe a problem like that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 634878.0,
      "end_time": 636680.0,
      "text": "you know you really have a problem."
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 638196.0,
      "end_time": 641863.0,
      "text": "And in the United Kingdom, the [2016] Brexit vote ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 642838.0,
      "end_time": 646326.0,
      "text": "you know, has divided a nation even more so."
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 647331.0,
      "end_time": 651109.0,
      "text": "And one critic of the breakup called those who favor it --"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 651133.0,
      "end_time": 652982.0,
      "text": "I just love this phrase --"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 653600.0,
      "end_time": 655971.0,
      "text": "\"the frightened parochial lizard brain of Britain.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 656417.0,
      "end_time": 659188.0,
      "text": "The frightened parochial lizard brain of Britain."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 659212.0,
      "end_time": 660362.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s personal."
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 661220.0,
      "end_time": 664576.0,
      "text": "And it makes me miss \"Downton Abbey\""
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 664600.0,
      "end_time": 666947.0,
      "text": "and its patina of civility."
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 668871.0,
      "end_time": 671180.0,
      "text": "But therein lies the third rule:"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 671204.0,
      "end_time": 673537.0,
      "text": "don&#39;t mistake decorum for civility."
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 674165.0,
      "end_time": 677982.0,
      "text": "Even if you have a dowager countess as fabulous as Dame Maggie Smith."
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 678600.0,
      "end_time": 679140.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 679380.0,
      "end_time": 680958.0,
      "text": "[Don&#39;t be defeatist. It&#39;s so middle class.]"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 680982.0,
      "end_time": 682954.0,
      "text": "So let me end with one last story."
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 683609.0,
      "end_time": 687297.0,
      "text": "Not that long ago, I was at a bakery, and they make these amazing scones."
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 687321.0,
      "end_time": 689613.0,
      "text": "So, long line -- there are a lot of scones."
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 689637.0,
      "end_time": 691733.0,
      "text": "And one by one, the scones were disappearing"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 691757.0,
      "end_time": 694589.0,
      "text": "until there was one woman in between me and that last scone."
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 694614.0,
      "end_time": 695764.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 696315.0,
      "end_time": 699570.0,
      "text": "Praise the Lord, she said, \"I&#39;ll have a croissant.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 699810.0,
      "end_time": 700315.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 700339.0,
      "end_time": 703236.0,
      "text": "So when it became my turn, I said, \"I&#39;ll take that scone.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 704814.0,
      "end_time": 706346.0,
      "text": "The guy behind me --"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 706370.0,
      "end_time": 708862.0,
      "text": "I&#39;d never turned around, never seen him --"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 708886.0,
      "end_time": 710499.0,
      "text": "he shouted, \"That&#39;s my scone!"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 711291.0,
      "end_time": 713132.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ve been waiting in line 20 minutes.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 713156.0,
      "end_time": 715683.0,
      "text": "And I was like, \"Who are you?"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 715707.0,
      "end_time": 718752.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ve been waiting in line 20 minutes, and you&#39;re behind me.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 718776.0,
      "end_time": 721234.0,
      "text": "So, I grew up here in New York,"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 721259.0,
      "end_time": 723625.0,
      "text": "and went to high school not that far from here."
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 723649.0,
      "end_time": 727315.0,
      "text": "And I may seem, you know, very civil here and so on,"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 727339.0,
      "end_time": 732961.0,
      "text": "but I can hip check anybody for a taxicab in this room, on these streets."
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 732985.0,
      "end_time": 735307.0,
      "text": "So I was surprised when I said to this guy ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 736398.0,
      "end_time": 738100.0,
      "text": "\"Would you like half?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 738250.0,
      "end_time": 739458.0,
      "text": "\"Would you like half?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 739482.0,
      "end_time": 741704.0,
      "text": "I didn&#39;t think about it, it just came out."
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 742600.0,
      "end_time": 745770.0,
      "text": "And then, he was very puzzled, and I could see his face change"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 745101.0,
      "end_time": 746291.0,
      "text": "and he said to me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 746315.0,
      "end_time": 749663.0,
      "text": "\"Well, how about if I buy another pastry and we&#39;ll share both of them?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 750665.0,
      "end_time": 753202.0,
      "text": "And he did, and we did."
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 753577.0,
      "end_time": 754977.0,
      "text": "And we sat and talked."
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 755539.0,
      "end_time": 757213.0,
      "text": "We had nothing in common."
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 757237.0,
      "end_time": 758617.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 758642.0,
      "end_time": 762868.0,
      "text": "We had nothing in common: nationality, sexual orientation, occupation."
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 763332.0,
      "end_time": 767705.0,
      "text": "But through this moment of kindness, through this moment of connection,"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 767729.0,
      "end_time": 770118.0,
      "text": "we developed a friendship, we have stayed in touch."
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 770142.0,
      "end_time": 771292.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 771316.0,
      "end_time": 774808.0,
      "text": "Although he was appalled to learn that I&#39;m called the Civilist after that."
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 774832.0,
      "end_time": 775982.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 776474.0,
      "end_time": 778874.0,
      "text": "But I call this the joy of civility."
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 779276.0,
      "end_time": 780442.0,
      "text": "The joy of civility."
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 780466.0,
      "end_time": 781808.0,
      "text": "And it led me to wonder,"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 781832.0,
      "end_time": 785370.0,
      "text": "what is the good we forgo, not just the trouble we avoid,"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 785610.0,
      "end_time": 786995.0,
      "text": "when we choose to be uncivil."
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 787958.0,
      "end_time": 791137.0,
      "text": "And by good, I mean friendship, I mean connection."
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 791161.0,
      "end_time": 793223.0,
      "text": "I mean sharing 1000 calories."
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 794336.0,
      "end_time": 796336.0,
      "text": "But I also mean it in a larger way."
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 796360.0,
      "end_time": 799428.0,
      "text": "You know, as communities and as a country and as a world."
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 800233.0,
      "end_time": 802320.0,
      "text": "What are we missing out on?"
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 802989.0,
      "end_time": 807886.0,
      "text": "So, today, we are engaged in a great civil war of ideas and identity."
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 807910.0,
      "end_time": 809910.0,
      "text": "And we have no rules for them."
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 810886.0,
      "end_time": 813153.0,
      "text": "You know, there are rules for war."
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 813618.0,
      "end_time": 815317.0,
      "text": "Think about the Geneva Conventions."
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 815341.0,
      "end_time": 817793.0,
      "text": "They ensure that every soldier is treated humanely,"
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 817817.0,
      "end_time": 819617.0,
      "text": "on and off the battlefield."
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 821372.0,
      "end_time": 824410.0,
      "text": "So, frankly, I think we need a Geneva Convention of civility,"
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 824434.0,
      "end_time": 827172.0,
      "text": "to set the rules for discourse for the parameters of that."
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 827776.0,
      "end_time": 832171.0,
      "text": "To help us become better citizens of our communities and of our countries."
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 833395.0,
      "end_time": 835268.0,
      "text": "And if I have anything to say about it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 835292.0,
      "end_time": 839690.0,
      "text": "I would base those rules on the original definition of civility,"
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 839930.0,
      "end_time": 841212.0,
      "text": "from the Latin and from the French."
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 841236.0,
      "end_time": 842982.0,
      "text": "Civility:"
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 843600.0,
      "end_time": 846913.0,
      "text": "citizens willing to give of themselves for the greater good."
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 847526.0,
      "end_time": 849193.0,
      "text": "For the good of the city."
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 849811.0,
      "end_time": 852938.0,
      "text": "So I think civility, with that understanding, is not a dirty word."
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 853534.0,
      "end_time": 858858.0,
      "text": "And I hope the civilist will not become, or will not stay, obsolete."
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 859667.0,
      "end_time": 860825.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 860849.0,
      "end_time": 865833.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}